task.summary: Default task
Add the GPS view to map fragment
Add the GPS view to map fragment
Add the GPS view to map fragment
Fix map GPS
Fix map GPS
Added location of tablet like Ioannis wanted. Fixed a bug that was causing some lag
Believe I made a temporary fix to the rotation problem. Again if someone could test it on their simulator to make sure that'd be great
Added ability to switch the centering of map on either the tablet, or the robot. Use single tap for robot and a longpress to center on tablet.
Just adding some comments
Moved a test class out of the actual app package and in to the test one
Fixed the back button issue he added this morning
Set the number of times back can be pressed to 2 before going back to robot chooser.
Added an About option to the Navigation drawer like I suggested the other day. Feel free to edit what it says as you see fit.
Fixed simple waypoint jerking movement.
Added framework for collision detection warning. If the laser scan layer determines that a collision is imminent, a callback in ControlApp is triggered. This isn't finished yet.

Made HUDFragment, JoystickFragment, and MapFragment use RobotController's subscribers instead of registering their own. Decreased the range of the LaserScanLayer and made point density decrease with range. Moved Robot pose information getters from HUDFragment to RobotController.
Made the LaserScanLayer scalable.
Fixed a bug in SimpleWaypointPlan that would cause it to ignore the emergency stop button. Moved the Emergency Stop button code into HUDFragment. Made the Waypoints draw more nicely.
Can start RobotPlan again after stopping them with the emergency stop button. Added some documentation.
Fixed bug with emergency stop button not working after switching between motion plans. Made the RobotController not reinitialize every time a fragment is switched out.
Altered the old LaserScanLayer system so that it doesn't use any of the ROS Visualization view which removed the need for an extra node and subscriber for LaserScan data.
The LaserScan view can be set so that the camera does not lock to the Robot's heading in which case the user can rotate it manually to any direction.
Fixed the beep beep warning system add made the HUDFragment flash red also.
Added a Preference item for enabling/disabling the warning system. Fixed a bug where topics wouldn't be reinitialized after being edited from the Preferences. Cleaned up strings.xml.
Added a 'safe mode' in which the Robot cannot drive into any walls. It can be disabled from Preferences. You can also disable the warning beeps.
Added a feature to move waypoints by long pressing them. Waypoints can also be inserted into the path by double tapping on an existing edge. Fixed the turn rate units in the HUDFragment.
HelpFragment quick fix. Also added Test class for Utils.
Added documentation. Increased the safe distance.
Added more instrumentation tests.
Formatted and updated the about page text.
Created templates for the three help tabs. Added documentation.
Fixed a bug with the emergency stop button when switching between views.
